As you can see `Selenium` `WebDriverWait` is set by default to poll the DOM every 500 milliseconds. We can override this setting with the use of `pollingEvery` method.  
This can be done as following:
```java
public WebElement waitVisibility(By by) {
    WebDriverWait wait = new WebDriverWait(driver, 40);
    wait.pollingEvery(200, TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS);
    return wait.until(ExpectedConditions.visibilityOfElementLocated(by));
}
```

To configure the _duration in milliseconds to sleep between polls_ you can use the following [_constructor_](https://www.selenium.dev/selenium/docs/api/java/org/openqa/selenium/support/ui/WebDriverWait.html#%3Cinit%3E(org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver,java.time.Duration,java.time.Duration)) of [WebDriverWait](https://stackoverflow.com/a/48990165/7429447):

